snippet.textDisplay: These type of games were never really given any official label to define their genre; they have merely been referred to as BreakOut-style games and Arkanoid clones through the decades, borrowed from the titles of those original games. I highly recommend you delve further into game music. It's a truly unique area of the musical spectrum and one that I've devoted myself to listening to since I was a child.

If you'd like some soundtrack recommendations, I've got a wide variety to choose from in mind:

Okami
The Binding of Isaac
The entire Kingdom Hearts series
Bastion 
Kirby and the Crystal Shards
and many more :D
